  "prompt": "What are the best free WordPress plugins in 2014?",
  "response": "In 2014, several free WordPress plugins were highly regarded for their functionality, ease of use, and support. Here are some of the best free WordPress plugins from that year:\n\n1. **Yoast SEO**: This plugin is essential for optimizing your WordPress site for search engines. It offers a comprehensive suite of tools for improving your on-page SEO, including content analysis, XML sitemaps, and meta tags.\n\n2. **Contact Form 7**: A very popular plugin for creating and managing contact forms. It is highly customizable and supports CAPTCHA, Akismet spam filtering, and various other features.\n\n3. **Akismet**: Developed by the creators of WordPress, Akismet is an anti-spam plugin that helps filter out spam comments. It's very effective and easy to use.\n\n4. **Jetpack**: This plugin offers a variety of features including site stats, social media sharing, related posts, and more. It's a versatile plugin that can enhance your site in many ways.\n\n5. **WooCommerce**: For those looking to build an online store, WooCommerce is the leading eCommerce plugin for WordPress. It provides extensive functionality for selling products and managing your online store.\n\n6. **W3 Total Cache**: This plugin helps improve your site's performance by caching pages and reducing load times. It's particularly useful for high-traffic sites.\n\n7. **Wordfence Security**: A robust security plugin that offers firewall protection, malware scanning, and live traffic monitoring to keep your site secure.\n\n8. **Google XML Sitemaps**: This plugin generates a special XML sitemap to help search engines index your site more effectively.\n\n9. **Broken Link Checker**: This plugin scans your site for broken links and missing images, helping you keep your site in good shape and improve user experience.\n\n10. **NextGEN Gallery**: A popular plugin for creating and managing galleries. It offers a range of gallery styles and customization options.\n\nThese plugins were highly recommended in 2014 for their reliability and the value they added to WordPress sites.",
